  "texts": [
    "Therefore, when consumers are well-informed, producers are encouraged to exercise optimal care, even without liability (Shavell, 1980).",
    "The rationale for extending product liability to include customers is that customers frequently lack adequate information regarding potential risks associated with products.",
    "When customers cannot accurately assess product risks, their purchasing decisions fail to reflect the actual level of risk involved.",
    "As a result, manufacturers lack incentives to exercise optimal care, as they bear no liability for any potential harm.",
    "Even if producers try to enhance product safety, these endeavours are not rewarded with increased sales as consumers fail to recognise the lower risk when purchasing."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}